{{short description|Australian philosopher}} {{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Simone Bignall''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Continental philosophy|Continental]] | institutions = [[Flinders University]] |main_interests = [[Postcolonialism]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | doctoral_advisor = [[Moira Gatens]] | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Sydney]] (PhD), [[University of Adelaide]] (BA) |influences = |influenced = |awards = }}
'''Simone Bignall''' is an Australian philosopher and Senior Lecturer of [[Philosophy]] at [[Flinders University]]. She is a former Chair of the [[Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy]] (2016-2018) and is now its Equity and Diversity Officer.<ref>{{cite web |title=Black Issues in Philosophy: Response to “Australian Continental Philosophy” |url=https://blog.apaonline.org/2018/01/09/black-issues-in-philosophy-response-to-australian-continental-philosophy/ |website=Blog of the APA |accessdate=14 October 2018 |date=9 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=History of the ASCP |url=https://www.ascp.org.au/about-the-ascp/history-of-the-ascp |website=Australasian Society for Continental Philosophy |accessdate=14 October 2018 |language=en-gb}}</ref> Bignall is known for her research on [[Postcolonialism]].
==Books== * ''Postcolonial Agency: Critique and Constructivism'' (Edinburgh 2010) * ''Posthuman Ecologies'' (with Rosi Braidotti, 2018) * ''Deleuze and the Postcolonial'' (with Paul Patton, 2010) * ''Agamben and Colonialism'' (with Marcelo Svirsky, 2012) * ''Deleuze and Pragmatism'' (with Sean Bowden and [[Paul R. Patton]], 2014) * ''Excolonialism: Ethics after Enjoymen''t, forthcoming
